COMPONENT NAME: RKM JDE Enterprise One Oracle COMPONENT VERSION: 10.1.3.0 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 10.1.3.5.0 and above
Description: - Reverse Knowledge Module. - Reverse engineering Knowledge Module to retrieve the tables for JDE Enterprise One.
Restrictions: - This RKM is suitable for JDE installed on Oracle.
Oracle Schema that store the JDE Central objects
Oracle Schema that store the JDE data dictionary
Oracle schema that store the JDE Object librarian
If this option is selected, data tables are reversed
If this option is selected, interface tables (ztables) are reversed

JDE System Short Name as (set % for all JDE System) : 00 Foundation Environment 01 Adress Book 02 Electronic Mail 03 Accounts Receivable etc ...
Or you can specify a list of modeles like '01','02','03'
Language used to recover the object description and comments. List of language : E English F French S Spanish

insert into SNP_REV_SUB_MODEL ( I_MOD, SMOD_CODE, SMOD_NAME
) values ( <%=snpRef.getModel("ID")%>, :SMOD_CODE, :SMOD_NAME )

insert into SNP_REV_SUB_MODEL ( I_MOD, SMOD_CODE, SMOD_NAME, SMOD_PARENT_CODE
) values ( <%=snpRef.getModel("ID")%>, :SMOD_CODE, :SMOD_NAME, :SMOD_PARENT_CODE )

insert into SNP_REV_TABLE (I_MOD, TABLE_NAME, RES_NAME, TABLE_ALIAS, TABLE_TYPE, TABLE_DESC, IND_SHOW,SMOD_CODE,R_COUNT) values (<%=snpRef.getModel("ID")%>, :TABLE_NAME, :RES_NAME, :TABLE_ALIAS, 'T', :TABLE_DESC, '1',:SMOD_CODE,:R_COUNT)

insert into SNP_REV_COL ( I_MOD, TABLE_NAME, COL_NAME, DT_DRIVER, COL_DESC,COL_HEADING, POS, LONGC,BYTES, SCALEC, COL_MANDATORY, CHECK_STAT, CHECK_FLOW) values ( <%=snpRef.getModel("ID")%>, :TABLE_NAME, :COL_NAME, :DT_DRIVER, :COL_DESC, :COL_HEADING, :POS, :LONGC,:LONGC, :SCALEC, :COL_MANDATORY, '0', '1')
insert into SNP_REV_KEY (I_MOD, TABLE_NAME, KEY_NAME, CONS_TYPE, IND_ACTIVE, CHECK_FLOW, CHECK_STAT) Values (<%=snpRef.getModel("ID")%>, :TABLE_NAME, :KEY_NAME, :CONS_TYPE, '1', '1', '1' )
insert into SNP_REV_KEY_COL ( I_MOD, TABLE_NAME, KEY_NAME, COL_NAME, POS) Values (<%=snpRef.getModel("ID")%>, :TABLE_NAME, :KEY_NAME, :COL_NAME, :POS)

insert into SNP_REV_SUB_MODEL ( I_MOD, SMOD_CODE, SMOD_NAME, SMOD_PARENT_CODE
) values ( <%=snpRef.getModel("ID")%>, :SMOD_CODE, :SMOD_NAME, :SMOD_PARENT_CODE )

insert into SNP_REV_COL ( I_MOD, TABLE_NAME, COL_NAME, DT_DRIVER, COL_DESC,COL_HEADING, POS, LONGC,BYTES, SCALEC, COL_MANDATORY, CHECK_STAT, CHECK_FLOW) values ( <%=snpRef.getModel("ID")%>, :TABLE_NAME, :COL_NAME, :DT_DRIVER, :COL_DESC, :COL_HEADING, :POS, :LONGC,:LONGC, :SCALEC, :COL_MANDATORY, '0', '1')
insert into SNP_REV_KEY (I_MOD, TABLE_NAME, KEY_NAME, CONS_TYPE, IND_ACTIVE, CHECK_FLOW, CHECK_STAT) Values (<%=snpRef.getModel("ID")%>, :TABLE_NAME, :KEY_NAME, :CONS_TYPE, '1', '1', '1' )
insert into SNP_REV_KEY_COL ( I_MOD, TABLE_NAME, KEY_NAME, COL_NAME, POS) Values (<%=snpRef.getModel("ID")%>, :TABLE_NAME, :KEY_NAME, :COL_NAME, :POS)
